@Mickacabra  

[Phelddagrif](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phelddagrif)/[Questing Phelddagrif](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Questing Phelddagrif) (anagram of Garfield, Ph. D; Richard Garfield, creator of Magic)  

The original phelddagrif is on the reserved list; I'm guessing the later version of it was meant to "work around" it.

@McThor  
I know, right? Everything else that makes Merfolk seems to make Merfolk Wizards ([Stonybrook Schoolmaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stonybrook Schoolmaster), [Summon the School](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Summon the School), etc.). That would have been an awesome combo. You can still get the same combo just by adding [Xenograft](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Xenograft) calling out Wizards.  

There are other things you could do to lock people out with [Lullmage Mentor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lullmage Mentor), like using [Intruder Alarm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Intruder Alarm), but you still have the problem of getting 7 Merfolk to begin with before getting slaughtered by removal / burn / pinging / etc., mass or otherwise.
